Comment: Hey this is a game that i played for the 61st Gk Tournament, round 5. It was a strong match with a tough opponent. Comments about the game are really welcomed! So i played with black ( i like white more but what can i do?). The game started with e4.
I played e5. I don't often play the sicilian cause e5 suits me better.
And then d4. Nice though most prefer to play Nf3.
I accepted the challenge and took the pawn.
Typical reply.
Open the knight and push the queen back.
Instead he played Qd5. I think Qd1 is better.
I open the other one knight. I wanted to develop all my pieces and hold a strong position.
Again not the greatest position for his queen i think.
I wanted to castled and though the position is quite pathetic i think is the best.
he developed the knight!
I castled and try now to develop the rest of my pieces.
c3? Playing Nc3 or Bd3 is better i think.
And now d5. Good move as i open the diagon for my bishop and also push the queen and the centre.
He took the pawn.
And i took it back with my knight.
g3? For me it's a bad move but ok if he's gonna play then Bg2.
Still his king is exposed and i wanted to check and attack( generally).
He should have played Be2 i guess.
And check.
